cards.description:
ST was being stupid with this, so I came up with a messy solution to a problem with the fonts. Preload them in your theme!
This card uses two different fonts, one for the human UI and one for the anthro UI. To make the fonts show, paste the following into the top of the custom CSS field in your theme settings:
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Charm&display=swap');
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Benne&display=swap');

Since the user's stats are set as variables early on in the chat, mixups might occur if the message where they're laid out goes out of context or is hidden.

Each part of the intro has its own tag that's sent with the AI response, things WILL get buggy if the AI forgets about it. I've put in a few guardrails to protect against this, but just so you know.

A single dice roll is done each reply, determining the success of your action. If the roll is lower than the attribute relevant to your action,  your action succeeds. A 0 is a critical success, and 11 is a critical failure. 

You can hover over the ability names in the player panel to show what they do.

For more cards by me, visit https://characterhub.org/users/illuminaryidiot or https://illuminaryidiot.neocities.org 
If you want to see the presets I use and test all my cards on, visit https://illuminaryidiot.neocities.org/presets

Originally, there was an XP system where you'd level up and get new class abilities each level based on your class. I cut this because it would be more fun for players to just have all the abilities at the start instead of having to "work" for them.

